------------------------------------------------------------------------
Derivative works contained in this repository
------------------------------------------------------------------------

The files under `references/` are not verbatim copies of the upstream
documentation. They are derivative markdown documents, restructured for
loading on demand by AI coding agents (Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, etc.).

Specifically, the following changes were made relative to the upstream
source pages listed in each file's frontmatter:

1. Rewritten lead paragraphs for brevity.
2. Added "Read this when ..." trigger sentences at the top of each file
   so an agent can decide whether to load the file based on the current
   task.
3. Preserved the upstream vocabulary tables, CLI flag tables, code
   examples, and API signatures — these are factual reference material
   and are reproduced from the upstream docs.
4. Omitted navigation chrome, page metadata, and marketing copy.
5. Collapsed some multi-section pages into a single markdown file per
   source URL.

No modifications were made to the HyperFrames code, CLI behavior, or
framework APIs. This repository contains documentation only.

